<div class="wrap">	<h2>Description</h2>	This plugin creats a listing of your posts/pages or categories.	You need to use shortcodes to embed a listing in your post/page	<br /><br />	<strong>Example shortcode usage</strong>	<ul>		<li>1. [atoz]</li>		<li>2. [atoz type="page"]</li>		<li>3. [atoz type="category" title="A-Z Category"]</li>		<li>4. [atoz type="post" title="A-Z" bg_color="#f0f0f0"]</li>		<li>5. [atoz type="post" title="A-Z" bg_color="#f0f0f0" text_color="#424242"]</li>	</ul>	Note:	<ul>		<li>type can be post/page or category [default is post]</li>		<li>title can be any anything that you wish you name your listing widget, use title=""</li>		<li>bg_color can be any hex color code, starts with #</li>		<li>text_color can be any hex color code, starts with #</li>	</ul>	Also all the settings can be changed from <a href="admin.php?page=alphabet-listing/alphabet_listing_settings.php">settings page</a>		<h2>Installation</h2>	Activate plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress	<h2>Remove plugin</h2>	<ul>		<li>1. Deactivate plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress</li>		<li>2. Delete plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress</li>	</ul>	It's best to use the built in delete function of wordpress. That way all the stored data will be removed and no orphaned data will stay.</div>